text: José Laureano Pineda Duarte (4 July 1802 in Rivas, Potosí, Rivas – 17 September 1853) was President (then called Supreme Director) of Nicaragua from 5 May to 11 August 1851, and later appointed as a dissident from 4 August, and from 11 November 1851 to 1 April 1853. ==References== Category:1802 births Category:1853 deaths Category:People from Rivas Department Category:Nicaraguan people of Spanish descent Category:Liberal Party (Nicaragua) politicians Category:Presidents of Nicaragua
title: Laureano Pineda
